author: malcolm
msg: Fix diff_tests 36 (wc->repos diff of added subtree).
Followup to r17234: if a directory was added, don't try to read its
properties.  Not only does it not have any, but we may get an error
when we try to read the parent's entries file if the parent directory
(close_directory): Explicitly set originalprops to an empty hash if
the directory was added instead of trying to load its properties.
Also, when diffing against BASE, don't allow the retrieval of an
access baton for a (non-added) directory to succeed by falling back to
the immediate parent's access baton (and hence obscure the problem).
